title: For Sale:  AK 5.56 with 2 scopes (Leupold and Lyman) and accessories
location: Santa Fe, NM, New Mexico, United States
postcontent:
This is an unusual AK variant. It is a pump action. Almost as fast to get multiple shots off as the semiauto versions, and is made on a real Milspec Ak receiver. Not a converted and chopped one like almost all semiauto imports are. Thus is is extremely accurate and reliable.

It is chambered in 5.56/223 and is flat shooting. I regularly shoot it at 475 yards with great success and occasionally out to 600. Same. Without the scope it makes a great self defense or plinking rifle. It always works because it is a pump. It is accurate because it is a pump. I have a custom ghost ring rear sight installed and it has about six inches longer sight radius than a regular AK. It is zeroed, and the front sight is fluorescent yellow. multiple front sights come with it too.

With either scope on it, it is a tack driver. Both scopes are mounted and zeroed on their own quick detachable rails. One is a vintage fixed 4 power Lyman All American. The rifle turned out to be so accurate that I installed a Leupold VariX-2  3-9x40 scope on a separate rail. It has been my go-to coyote rifle with that scope on it.

The rifle currently has a folding stock on it which is longer than the standard AK fixed stock. The fixed stock has the original buttplate under a one inch extended pad. No matter your size you should be able to fit this rifle to you. I prefer the folding stock because it gives proper eye relief with both of the scopes and the ghost ring. Your choice though.

There are also four Circle Ten 20 round magazines (highest quality) and the original two hunting magazines. The Circle Ten mags are about $30 apiece, and are fitted to this rifle perfectly. I have never had one single malfunction of any kind with it.

I probably have close to $1000 invested in this rifle, but my shooting and collecting tastes have changed.

Contact me through Armslist with your phone number and we can arrange to meet so you can see this. I think you will like it very much. If you are a too far away to come in person, I can ship to a New Mexico resident without using an FFL. I would need your driver's license. most people don't know that, so I just thought I would throw it out there. I can also ship out of state to you through an FFL. If you want to use a credit card, that can be arranged by using a discreet online payment. Shipping would be about $25.00.

If you have read this far, thank you very much for taking the time to read my very long ad!

All the best.

There has never been a higher demand for self defense handguns than there is today. The greatest demand is for the smallest, lightest gun available, but this has drawbacks. Generally these guns are difficult to shoot well, lack stopping power and recoil can be a problem. If you can’t hit or stop what you are shooting at, what good is the handgun? We can understand all of these concerns as we face them every day as well. We wanted to give our customers the smallest, lightest gun that we could without sacrificing accuracy, dependability and stopping power. Presenting the ECO, a true single stack officer size 1911 weighing in at only 25 oz. For years the officer 1911 has been criticized for reliability. We have taken care of that by using some of the latest technology as well as our background in doing what others say can’t be done. This gun has all the latest and greatest we have to offer. The ECO wears tritium night sights with our tactical ledge sight on the rear of our lightweight 3.5” slide. The barrel is a flush-cut ramped bull barrel with target crown rather than the traditional barrel and barrel bushing. This makes the gun slightly more compact and easier to disassemble. The recoil system is quite unique for this style of 1911 as we use a solid, one piece guide rod and a flat recoil spring that is rated for 15,000 rounds in .45 ACP. That is 15,000 rounds! Not 500 rounds like most 1911 dual recoil systems are rated for. This is unheard of in a production 1911! This recoil system also gives the benefit of a smooth slide for easier operation and less felt recoil. Trigger pull, like all of our 1911s, is short and crisp at around 4 lbs. This helps achieve the accuracy you’ve come to expect from a Dan Wesson. The frame is anodized aluminum and features an undercut trigger guard and 25 LPI checkering. The mainspring housing is also aluminum with 25 LPI checkering and a rounded bottom corner for concealability and shooting comfort. These features coupled with the Ed Brown high ride grip safety and our new slim line DW carry G10 grips really help you hold onto the gun for faster follow-up shots and recoil control. Just like our Guardian, the ECO slide and small parts are treated with our Duty finish and available in both 9mm and .45 ACP. Stopping power is not a concern. This is a very nice Browning 12 ga.  BPS shotgun that looks like new.  It has a 28" barrel fixed modified choke and the stock has no blemishes or scuff marks and show high gloss polish.  

BPS. A solid steel reputation for durability and dependability.
Few firearms ever earn the level of respect the Browning BPS boasts. The BPS has a solid reputation for long-lasting durability and an uncanny ability to keep on working in spite of what Mother Nature does to stop it. This shouldn’t come as a surprise because the BPS has what most other pump shotguns don’t — features like rigid dual machined steel action bars, a forged and machined steel receiver, a convenient top-tang safety and bottom ejection for ambidextrous operation, and legendary Browning balance and handling. That’s why the BPS continues to be the pump shotgun serious shotgunners like you can always rely on.

Ambidextrous. That is how many shooters describe the BPS. And it is true. But the advantages are more than just being a great shotgun for the left- OR right-handed shooter. The bottom ejection design and full, two-sided steel receiver combine for a level of durability and strength that is not common among pump action shotguns today. The design is totally balanced, with matching dual steel slide action bars -- one on each side -- that balance forces for very smooth pumping. Top tang safety is functional convenience to the max. The receiver forms a "roof" over the action-- there is no opening on either side for an ejection port, so a drenching rain won't drip into the action. When you shoot bottom ejection makes sure there are no empties flying to the side, across your line of sight,  to distract your aim. Those that shoot a BPS are a unique bunch . . . a bit more serious about their hunting guns than most? Yes!

Bottom Ejection and Loading
Bottom ejection throws empty shells straight down, out of the line of sight, and makes the BPS the ultimate pump for right- or left-handed shooters. Bottom loading provides operating convenience.

Reliable Pump-Action
The proven pump-action design of the BPS is sound and reliable. All components are durably constructed of solid steel and are housed inside a receiver machined from a solid block of forged steel. Rigid double slide bars are made from heat-treated steel and eliminate twisting and binding for faster, more efficient operation. The result is smooth operation in all conditions and the ability to stay on target while delivering rapid follow-up shots. A convenient serrated slide release is located at the rear of the trigger guard.

Safety
The thumb-operated, top-tang safety on the BPS can be easily operated by right- and left-handed shooters alike, even with gloved fingers.

Magazine Capacity
2 3/4": Four in magazine, one in chamber. 3": Three in magazine, one in chamber. 3 1/2": Three in magazine, one in chamber. A three-shot magazine adapter plug is included.

Back-Bored Barrels
12 and 20 gauge BPS shotguns feature Back-Bored Technology.

title: For Sale:  MOD 1 - Handgun Basic Skills Builder Class **MAY 25, 2014**
postcontent:
Warm weather is finally here so it's time to hit the range and push lead!!

If you have, or are planning on getting, your Concealed Carry Permit then you NEED to take this class. This class will teach you how to carry, shoot and think correctly. 

**This is NOT the class you need for your Colorado Handgun Permit certificate.***

If you need your cert them please let me know!

Carrying a handgun is a HUGE responsibility. Most people don't truly understand that! This class will teach you the correct way to not only carry correctly but also how to come out of your holster and get off the first shots accurately before the bad guy does. You also will learn to shoot at multiple targets while moving. This training should be mandatory for anyone that carries a gun. When you finish this class you WILL have a lot more confidence with your handgun handling. 

This class is our Basic Defensive Handgun Skills Builder Class held at the Pawnee Sportsman's Center near Briggsdale!! 

CLASS DATE is **SUNDAY MAY 25, 2014** 9a-5p
Class is limited to only (20) Shooters!!

This class is (7) hours long - 9a-5p

We will cover the following drills:
- Safely Loading & Unloading the Firearm
- Proper Grip and Stance
- Trigger Control
- After Action Drills
- Tactical and Emergency Reloading
- Clearing Malfunctions
- Presentation from the Holster
- Controlled Pair Shots
- Designated Headshots
- Moving and Shooting
- Moving and Shooting Multiple Targets
- Shooting One Handed
- And a whole lot more!!

The course fee is $75 plus a range fee of $25 per person. 

REQUIRED equipment: 
- Belt Holster (right or left side only) 
- 200 rounds of target/practice ammo 
- Eyes and ears protection (Mandatory) 
- Clothing recommendations: 
* Boots or sturdy shoes - (NO OPEN TOE SHOES ALLOWED)
* Long pants and tight neck shirt 
- hot brass does not feel good going down your shirt!!
* Baseball style hat
* Extra clothes for the ever changing weather we have here in Colorado 
- WE WILL NOT STOP SHOOTING UNLESS WE SEE OR HEAR LIGHTNING!
- Sunscreen 
- Plenty of water or Gatorade 
- Lunch and snacks 
- Chair to sit in during down times

The purpose of this class is to get you extremely comfortable with your gun.

We will be working on the basic shooting fundamentals. When you leave this class you should be able to draw your handgun, from your holster, and fire an accurate shot on target in less than 1.5 seconds!!

We only have (20) limited spots for shooters - so, please sign up early!!

If you have any questions you can reach Jim (the instructor) at 
Jim (at) SafetyTrainingInstitute (dot) us or call or text him at 303 / 500 / 3309 



A little about your instructor: 

Jim Roshan has been a concealed handgun permit holder for over 25 years. He hold most of the NRA firearms Instructor disciplines including several Law Enforcement Instructor Certifications. He is a Colorado POST Certified Law Enforcement Firearms Instructor. He also is a Licensed Training Provider for the American Red Cross. Safety Training Institute regularly holds several ARC First Aid and CPR classes too.

Being a full-time firearms and EMS instructor, Jim's ability to 'teach' you what you need to know is far superior to any other part-time instruction you can find. Being in Law Enforcement also adds a ton of value to his classes. You will learn how "it" needs to be done correctly!

So, if you have been putting off learning how to use your gun defensively NOW is your chance to finally check this off your list!

SIGN UP AT SafetyTrainingInstitute (dot) us!!!
